  "title": "Senior Production Supervisor #81369",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p><ul><li>Industry/ Organization Type: Manufacturer – Dairy Products</li><li>Position Title: <strong>Senior Production Supervisor / Production Supervisor</strong></li><li>Working Location: Tuas</li><li>Working Hours: 5 days (Mon to Fri: 8:00am – 8.00pm)</li><li>Salary Package: <strong>Basic + AWS + Performance Bonus</strong></li><li>Duration: Permanent</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Run the factory when the Factory Manager is away.</li><li>Lead and support Production Supervisors and Line Leaders; drive performance and accountability.</li><li>Plan and manage 12-hour rotating shifts (day/night), including weekends and public holidays.</li><li>Ensure effective training and coaching for new Operators and Line Leaders.</li><li>Meet daily production volume and efficiency targets.</li><li>Drive continuous improvement to boost productivity, quality, and safety.</li><li>Make sure teams follow all work instructions, equipment rules, and quality standards.</li><li>Ensure full compliance with Safety, GMP, and Quality policies; coordinate general waste collection and recycling (pallets and paper bags).</li><li>Oversee and check product sample collection to meet quality/lab requirements.</li><li>Ensure accurate and on-time production records and Navision entries.</li><li>Maintain high housekeeping and 5S standards across the site.</li><li>Ensure strong working knowledge of batching, dumping, and packing equipment (self and team).</li><li>Plan and manage maintenance, including basic repairs by Line Leaders, to reduce downtime.</li><li>Resolve major technical issues; support first-line troubleshooting and escalate to Engineering/Management only when needed.</li><li>Perform other duties as assigned.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>APPLY NOW!!!</strong></p><ul><li>At least 5–7 years in manufacturing/factory operations in a similar environment.</li><li></li></ul><p>Kindly apply through <strong>ANY </strong>of the following methods:</p><ul><li>Submit your application by clicking the <strong>APPLY </strong>button;</li><li>Email your resume to <a href=\"mailto:Job@anradus.com.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Job@anradus.com.sg</a>. Please indicate <strong>#81369 </strong>on the email subject.</li><li></li></ul><p><strong>Anradus Application Policy:</strong> We value each application and ensure every resume is reviewed. Our process is efficient, typically concluding within <strong>3 working days</strong>. If you do not receive communication from us within this timeframe, it's likely that your application has not been shortlisted by our client. In such cases, we recommend continuing your job search to maximize your opportunities.</p><p><br /><br /></p><p>Anradus Pte Ltd | EA License No. 20C0161 | Angel Lim | EA Reg No.: R1769781</p>",
